      "sc:description": "Benchmark of tools for CNV detection from NGS panel data in a genetic diagnostics context.\n\nFull-spectrum copy number variation detection by high-throughput DNA sequencing.\n\nHigh-throughput DNA sequencing enables detection of copy number variations (CNVs) on the genome-wide scale with finer resolution compared to array-based methods, but suffers from biases and artifacts that lead to false discoveries and low sensitivity.\n\nYuchao Jiang yuchaoj@email.unc.edu.\n\n||| NAME (CODEX2) SIMILAR TO (PUB. DIFFERENT) bio.tools/codex_ngs (CODEX), bio.tools/codex (CODEX).\n\n||| CORRECT NAME OF TOOL COULD ALSO BE 'DECoN', 'CNV', 'panelcn', 'Benchmarking-optimization'",
